1. Complete the ternary expression to display the button text based on the value of the isLoggedIn state.
- ?, :

2. Complete the code to add the method that will clear the interval ID once the component gets removed from the DOM.
- return

3. In the code snippet below when will React run the console.log statement?
const Message = () => {
    const [name, setName] = useState();

    useEffect(() => {
        console.log("hello " + name);
    });

    return (...);
}
- After the first render and after each render

4. Which of the following are appropriate use cases for the useEffect Hook? (Select all that apply)
- Directly updating the DOM, Setting up a subscription, Setting up timers, Fetching data

5. In the code snippet below when will React run the console.log statement?
const Message = () => {
    const [name, setName] = useState();

    useEffect(() => {
        console.log("hello " + name);
    }, []);

    return (...);
}
- After the first render only

6. In the code snippet below when will React run the console.log statement?
const Message = () => {
    const [name, setName] = useState();

    useEffect(() => {
        console.log("hello " + name);
    }, [name]);

    return (...);
}
- After the first render and every time the name state updates